<br>
I’ve been on several Hate raids lately, and the Word has always been, NO PETS.  Why?  Oh why?  They fear the pet will cause trains.  We, as mages, know the safe wall is safe for a pet.  We’re all professionals here.  We all know the tricks of the trade.  We’ve all ready Kylere’s post, and we all knew it before we read it.  /pet guard here, /pet back off, Earthen Boots for insta-pet death.  By the time you’re in your 50’s this is ingrained.<br>
<br>
We know how to control our pets.  So why don’t others trust us?  A mage without a pet is so useless.  Any other offensive class would be better on a Hate raid.  Any.  I nuke once, maybe twice, for a total of 1340 pts of damage.  My pet could do at least that much damage.  Perhaps twice as much.  I’m dead weight, just tagging along hoping for a piece of Apothic.  How demeaning.  How insulting.  I KNOW how to control my pet!  Do NOT tell me how to play my class!  I did NOT buy this character on eBay, I sweated though all 53 levels.<br>
<br>
We are not trusted to control our own pets, something we have done for, perhaps, years.  Pathing at the safe wall is acceptable.  Pets will not follow the wacky pathing that the mobs do.  /assist tank, wait to verify you’ve got the right one, yes, the tank’s clearly swinging at that mob right there, and yes, the mob’s name is flashing, /pet attack.  Pet runs straight to mob, kills it, and then comes straight back to the guard spot.  Simple.  We’ve all seen this before.  I have.  So have the very same raid leaders who have now, mysteriously, decided that pets are no longer welcome.<br>
<br>
Again, I’m talking about the safe wall here.  Yes, there may be places in Hate where pets are a no-no, and moving with pets is right-out.  But the safe wall is safe for a pet.<br>
<br>
I believe myself to be an excellent pet controller.  I do not cause trains, I always assist, and I never break mez.  Even if my view is flawed, I couldn’t be worse than an average pet controller.  I’m certainly not a bad one.  But yet, I am untrusted to do something I’ve done since level 4.<br>
<br>
Kylere made that post about what he told his guild.  That’s great, the way he posted it implies that they listened to him.  Unfortunately, my guild does not listen to me (and I am an officer).  They do not believe me.  They do not believe that the added risk of the pet is worth it – they do not understand the added benefit of the pet.  With the changes in Hate, a runner could easily cause a train (thus, wipeout).  What better way to stop a runner than a few Earth pets?  Doesn’t matter.<br>
<br>
I am the second highest person in my guild.  There is one higher.  He is a level 55 mage.  He, of course, disagrees completely with me.  He is perfectly happy to go to Hate without his pet.  He feels pets in Hate are too dangerous (though he’s used them in the past – what happened?!).  We have a Hate raid coming up, and he has said point blank that if pets are allowed on the raid, he and his uber-friends aren’t coming.  Others outside the guild have said the same.  This utterly baffles me that a fellow mage and guildmate would say such a thing.  Tensions between us have gotten to the point where I cannot ask him questions about this.<br>
<br>
I do not enjoy spending 8-12 hours as an ineffective, defenseless excuse for a level 40 wizard.  Why would anyone?  Yes, there is the lure of the Apothic.  But wouldn’t it be so much more fun to be up there with your pet, doing significant damage, helping out, getting your group some xp, and maybe even doing emergency crowd control?  Generally contributing something to the raid?  Like we’re used to?  (In non uber-encounters, anyway.  /sigh).<br>
<br>
Are we that hard to understand?  Leaders do not seem to understand how much we can contribute to a raid with our pets, and how little we do when we don’t have our pets.<br>
<br>
This problem has bothered me immensely.  I feel as though I need to take some drastic action.  Either retiring my mage outright, leaving my guild for one that respects mages, or perhaps even quitting EQ and getting on with my life.<br>
<br>
Thank you, your comments are welcome.<br>
<br>
Balasarius<br>
